The police officer went missing shortly after five firearms, which he signed out, disappeared in January. JOHANNESBURG - Eastern Cape police are searching for one of their own who s apparently on the run after allegedly stealing guns.The Dimbaza-based constable, had been placed in charge of firearms to be tested at the SAPS forensic unit, in Port Elizabeth.The guns were meant to be been handed in there, but they never made it to Port Elizabeth.The police officer went missing shortly after five firearms, which he signed out, disappeared in January.The illegal guns were confiscated from raids conducted by police in Dimbaza.Police have confirmed one of the weapons has been recovered but there's still no sign of the constable.Cases of theft and defeating the ends of justice have been opened against him. He also faces disciplinary action.